data.enText: kept at a very low temperature in order to preserve it

before.enText: of people or parts of the body

data.enText: with a layer of ice on the surface
so cold that it has become very hard
unable to move because of a strong emotion such as fear or horror
She stared at him, frozen with shock.

ex.enText: He was swimming in cold water.

synonyms.bx: 最普通用词，指温度很低的，可用于形容天气或事物。

ex.chText: 屋内没有暖气，你会感觉冷飕飕的。
ex.enText: There is no heater in the room, so you may feel chilly.

synonyms.bx: 指天气或地方冷得让人不舒服的，程度介于 cool 和 cold 之间。

ex.chText: 我们一起度过了一个凉爽的夜晚。
ex.enText: We spent a cool night together.

ex.chText: 葡萄酒应贮存在阴凉的地下室里。
ex.enText: Wine should be stored in a cool cellar.

synonyms.bx: 指温度偏低但让人感到舒服的。

ex.chText: 天气太冷了，她感到寒冷刺骨。
ex.enText: It was so cold that she felt frozen to the bone.

ex.chText: 地面一整年都冻得硬邦邦的。
ex.enText: The ground was frozen solid for a whole year.

ex.chText: 你可以使用新鲜或冷冻的肉。
ex.enText: You can use fresh or frozen meat.

synonyms.bx: 指人冻僵的，或河流、地面等冻住的；也可指食物冷冻的。

ex.chText: 外面正刮着凛冽的寒风。
ex.enText: There was an icy wind blowing outside.

ex.chText: 她步入冰凉的水中时倒抽了一口冷气。
ex.enText: She gasped as she stepped into the icy water.

ex.chText: 她的鞋湿透了，冰冷冰冷的。
ex.enText: Her shoes were soaked and icy cold.

synonyms.bx: 多指水、风等寒冷刺骨的；也可说 icy cold。

tr: incapable of being changed or moved or undone
(used of foods) preserved by freezing sufficiently rapidly to retain flavor and nutritional value
affected by freezing or by long and severe cold
example: children skating on a frozen brook
a frozen look on their faces

value.def: If the ground is frozen it has become very hard because the weather is very cold.

example.ex: It was bitterly cold now and the ground was frozen hard.
example.tran: 现在天气冷极了，地面都冻硬了。

example.ex: ...the frozen bleakness of the Far North.

value.def: Frozen food has been preserved by being kept at a very low temperature.

example.ex: Frozen fish is a very healthy convenience food.
example.tran: 冻鱼是非常健康的方便食品。

value.def: If you say that you are frozen, or a part of your body is frozen, you are emphasizing that you feel very cold.

example.ex: He put one hand up to his frozen face...
example.tran: 他用一只手捂在冰冷的脸上。

example.ex: I'm frozen to the bone out here.
It was cold and damp; he pulled up his collar and was aware of being frozen stiff.
example.tran: 天气阴冷潮湿;他把衣领竖起来，感觉自己要被冻僵了。

value.tran: (人或身体某部位)冻坏的，冻僵的

value.def: If you describe someone as frozen, you mean that their body is fixed in a particular position, for example because they are very worried or afraid.

example.ex: One boy, aged about 11, looks frozen with fright...
example.tran: 一个大约 11 岁的男孩吓得一动不动。

value.tran: (因非常担心、害怕等而)呆若木鸡的，一动不动的

trans: 冷凍蔬菜；冷冻蔬菜；速冻蔬菜；德国求购蔬菜；求购蔬菜
冰封王座；寒冰王座；冰封宝座
